description:
The University of Messina (UniME) is located in Sicily, in the city of Messina. It was founded in 1548 an it is one of the oldest universities in Italy. UniME enjoys a long tradition as a driving force in the Mediterranean area and is strongly committed to growth as evident in its policy of internationalization and expansion.  It has a strong international component, with agreements from all over the world.  Exchange programmes, double degree and joint-degree programmes are all part of the international opportunities available to students. Because of the European Credit Transfer System, students may earn credits and take exams while they are studying abroad.  The University has 12 Departments, 94 degree programmes including 12  taught in English.  There are 15 Ph.D. Programmes, 21 Vocational 1-year Master degrees.

UniME currently has a student population of more than 15,000 students, coming from 70 different countries. There are 1100 professors, including 16 from foreign countries.

The degree programmes taught in English are as follows:

1) Six-year single cycle degree programme in Medicine and Surgery;

2) Bachelor's degree in Civil engineering

3) Bachelor's degree in data analysis

4) Bachelor's degree in Political Sciences and International Relations

5) Master's Degree in Cognitive science and theory of communication;

6) Master's Degree in Engineering and Computer Science;

7)  Master's Degree in Condensed Matter Physics;

8) Master's Degree in Geophysical Sciences and Seismic Risk;

9) Master's Degree in Data Science

10) Vocational Master in Banking and Finance.

11) Vocational Master in Food, Quality and International Management

12) Vocational Master in Airline management and regulation of the aviation industry

All degree programmes are taught by highly qualified professors with extensive international experience, they are job-oriented and students the possibility to carry out a traineeship in Italy or abroad.

Tashkent State Transport University is organized in accordance with the Resolution of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan dated May 4, 2020 No PP-4703 on the basis of the Ministry of Transport of the Republic of Uzbekistan, the Ministry of Higher and Secondary Special Education and the Tashkent Institute of Railway Engineers, Tashkent Institute of Design, Construction and Maintenance of Automobile Roads and the Faculty of Aerospace Technology of Tashkent State Technical University in order to radically improve the system of training highly qualified personnel for the transport sector of the Republic on the basis of advanced foreign experience and international standards, widespread introduction of innovative forms and methods of teaching and modern pedagogical and information technologies, as well as strengthening the material and technical base and scientific potential of the field.The university includes 8 faculties and 39 departments.

University:

• is a basic higher education institution for the training, retraining and qualifying highly educated specialists and researchers in the field of transport;

• gradually introduces the credit-module system of education from the 2020/2021 academic year in accordance with advanced international educational standards and curricula;

• is administratively dependent on the Ministry of Transport of the Republic of Uzbekistan.

The main tasks and functions of the University:

• training, retraining and qualifying competitive higher education specialists and scientific-pedagogical staff, as well as mass professionals, based on the needs of the transport sector;

• carrying out fundamental, practical and innovative research and studies on the key issues of transport development, implementing the results and putting forward proposals on widespread introduction of digital and other modern technologies;

• developing cooperation with leading foreign higher education and research institutions in order to implement joint educational programs and research projects, improve the skills of university professors and organize the study of graduates in master’s and doctoral programs abroad;

• creating a continuous system of training for the transport sector, ensuring the continuity and flow of educational programs in the academic lyceums and professional educational institutions of the field;

• organizing student internships in relevant organizations, establishing targeted cooperation for the employment of graduates together with organizations in the field of transport in order to provide an inextricable connection of theoretical training with practice.

HISTORY OF UMKThe establishment of a university in Kelantan was made as a component in the Ninth Malaysia Plan to support the quality of human capital development in the higher education sector. The federal agreement was announced by the Prime Minister on the 31 March 2006 in the Ninth Malaysia Plan proposal.The establishment of the university was approved in the Cabinet Meeting on 14 June 2006. The cabinet has specified that the philosophy of the curriculum in UMK should be based on entrepreneurship and enterprise education in all the study programmes.

Therefore, taglines such as "Entrepreneurship is Our Thrust" and "Entrepreneurial University" are widely used to promote the philosophy of this university. Specialised studies for short and moderate term are grouped into three main fields of studies, namely:

1. Entrepreneurship and Business;

2. Creative Technology and Heritage;

3. Agro-Based Industry and Earth Sciences

Apart from the three fields of studies, the significant emphasis would be given to acquiring languages and the development of soft skills. These learning programs aim is to produce high-quality human capital with a first class mentality and exemplary entrepreneurship attributes. It is hoped that this would contribute to the global prosperity by improving the capability and capacity of Small and Medium Enterprises (SME), and also towards the development of a highly entrepreneurial commercial society. In line with all areas of study, Information and Communication Technology (ICT) is employed as an enabler.

.The University of Sousse was created in 2004 from a division of the University of the Center, which had been created in 1991 from the University of Monastir. The University of the Center had grown rapidly from 45,000 students in 2001-2002 to nearly 60,000 in 2003-2004 in 30 institutions. In 2004 new universities were created in Monastir, Kairouan and Gafsa.

The University of Sousse has 17 higher education institutions (four faculties, four schools and nine institutes):

- Faculty of Law and Political Sciences;

- Medical School ;

- Faculty of Arts and Humanities;

- Faculty of Economics and Management;

- High School of Agronomy;

- National School of Engineering;

- Higher School of Science and Technology (Hammam Sousse);

- Institute of Health Sciences and Technology;

- Institute of Comercial Studies Institute ;

- Institute of Finance and Taxation;

- Institute of management ;

- Institute of Informatics and Communication Technologies (Hammam Sousse);

- Institute of Music;

- Institute of Fine Arts;

- Institute of Applied Science and Technology;

- Institute of Nursing Sciences;

- Institute of Transport and Logistics.

Tracing its history back to 1876, when it was created as the 9th Teacher's Training Institute in Russia, Belgorod State University (BelSU) has had quite a challenging history, and now it is one of the leading universities in Russia (21st in the Interfax National University Ranking) and is ranked by the major international university ranking agencies:

-   167 – QS World University Ranking: EECA 2020;

-   195 – QS World University Ranking: BRICS 2019.

-   76-100 – Global Ranking of Academic Subjects (ARWU), Metallurgical Engineering ;

-   1001+ – Times Higher Education World  University Ranking 2020;

-   301-400 – Times Higher Education Engineering and Technology Subject Ranking 2020;

-   601-800 – Times Higher Education Physical Sciences Subject Ranking 2020;

-   301-350 – Times Higher Education Emerging Economies University Rankings 2020.

Belgorod State University has campuses in Belgorod and Stary Oskol (Belgorod region). The Belgorod campus includes 9 institutes, 1 faculty, and an engineering college.

In 2020, the University offers 22 first long undivided degree (Specialist) programs, 138 bachelor’s degree programs, 124 master’s degree programs, over 100 post-graduate programs (both PhD and higher doctorate degrees), and 31 residency training programs for medical graduates.

The Quality System Management at Belgorod State University is recognized by its partners from 35 countries using IQNet (USA, France, Belgium, Portugal, China, Germany, Austria, etc.): designing, developing and carrying out educational activities in the spheres of high, higher, postgraduate and additional professional education, research and innovations.

Apart from having perfectly equipped classrooms and laboratories, the University is happy to offer its students a wide range of facilities: a huge Svetlana Khorkina’s sports complex, an equestrian sport school, the Botanical Garden and a winter garden, The Youth Cultural Center with its 17 student performance groups (dancing groups, music bands, theatre clubs, chorus, brass band, etc.), The Nezhegol Recreational Complex, to name just a few. Besides, the University has its own Saint Gabriel’s Church.

You will be able to try out all these and many other opportunities, enjoying a moderate Russian climate – with mild winters and sunny summers – and a hospitable and safe environment, with over 3,000 international students already studying at BelSU.

So if you want to experience a unique mixture of academic excellence, innovative research  and personal development, welcome to Belgorod State University!
